inn1.comm: Good first ball. Roach has this knack of bowling yorkers right away with the new ball. This one tails down leg, the batsman tries to jab it away and it rolls off the pad ..
Some swing on offer. Big swing  actually. It veered in from outside off stump, full and ends up on the middle, pushed out on the front foot
this one straightens outside off from short of length, left alone. Three different deliveries so far.
This one too is different all right - A wide down the leg side!
full pitched outside off stump, pushed out towards mid-off. Not timed .. the ball rolls away
Another wide down the leg side. There is some swing out there and Roach is having some trouble containing it
starts off from outside off this time and again the ball curves in appreciably to move past the defensive prod and bounds off the pad to short-leg
a shout for lbw but the ball was going down the leg side. He needs to get the trajectory starting from outside off if he wants to bowl those off cutters
full pitched outside off stump, driven away to wide third man region
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
lands on a length outside off, comes in a bit, nothing alarming and the batsman shoulders arms

Rampaul takes out Masakadza. Big early blow this. What a cracker of a delivery. It landed short of length and suddenly reared up sharply chest-high of the startled and out of position Masakadza who just stabbed it behind.
lets this one go through to Ramdin
runs it down to third man for a single
goes for the yorker, just about dug out to the on side
Roach is unable to control the big inward movement he is getting. Big big wide down the leg side. He stands at the end of the run-up, head bowed down
full and well outside off stump this time and this one doesn't move back in .... easily left alone
big in swing this time, starts from outside off and ends on the leg stump, rolls away off the pad to backward square-leg region

full and outside off, tilts in, the batsman shoulders arms ... could turn out risky as couple of Indian batsmen found against Dale Steyn who knocked out the off stump couple of times in a Test in India recently
short in length, climbs, steered to backward point
well outside off stump, left alone
homing in on the off stump, defended out to the off side
back of length, a tad wide outside off, left alone
moves in to the middle and off line, Sibanda leans forward to defend
kicks up outside off and Ramdin collects it over his left shoulder .. good carry
in the channel outside off stump, left alone
bounces from short of length outside off, guided out to point
First real authoritative shot of the day. Maruma plays a neat straight drive to the on side of the pitch past the non striker
full and outside off, holds its line this time and Maruma is beaten, pushing inside the line.. He was expecting Roach would bring this one back in too
overpitched outside off stump, square driven to Pollard at point
around that off stump, Maruma gets behind the line to defend
good delivery in the channel outside off, again holding its line and Maruma is beaten.. he just about pulls his bat away from the line
straightens outside off and Ramdin collects
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
around the off stump line, Sibanda gets forward, bat and pad close together as he pushes it out to the off side
Shot! It was a length delivery and some width on offer outside off, Sibanda moved forward and just slapped it on the up through cover
full in length, much closer to the off stump, Sibanda respects the line this time and lets it go
kicks up from short of length, just outside off stump, defended on the front foot
off cutter, moves in, moves past the batsman who lets it go, moves past the off stump and lands once before it reaches the keeper
full and moving in towards the middle and off line, defended on the front foot
full delivery outside off stump, square driven to point.
on the middle stump line this time, pushed past the non-striker
bounces from short of length, Maruma adjusts to the extra bounce and jabs it back down the track
Fuller one and on the middle, Maruma on drives it to the right of the diving mid-on
short in length, cuts in from outside off, steered to left of backward point ... the throw comes in from Pollard .. misses the stumps and gets past the diving fielder who tries to back up
full in length, moves in to the middle and off line, pushed back down the track, Rampaul dives and gets a hand on it and the ball dislodges the bails on the other end
bounces from short of length, on the middle stump line, stabbed to the on side ..
around that off stump line, pushed out to the off side
full in length, just outside off stump, steered to backward point
short in length and bounces in to move past the prod and strikes the thigh pad

Run out of Maruma missed. It was pushed towards backward point and Sibanda calls Maruma, who responds very late, for a single .. Pollard rushes on, stops and fires a throw at the non-striker's end with Maruma out of the frame but misses the stumps

Wicket first ball for Bravo. It landed on a length around off stump and Maruma leaned forward to defend. and the ball bounces rather late and bounds off the handle towards gully. Sammy dives forward to take a good catch
gets forward to push the ball away
leans forward to flick the ball to square-leg
on a length, around the middle stump line, turned to the on side
in the channel outside off stump, left alone
full in length and in the channel outside off, left alone

Clatter..........The off stump has gone for a nice little walk. It was full, it started from outside off and moved in late. Brendon Taylor is very late in getting forward and leaves a big gaping hole between bat and pad. mistake! Timber!
short in length and outside off stump, left alone
And again.
on the off stump line, defended to the leg side
Full in length and outside off stump, square driven firmly through the off-side field
outside off stump and moves away, left alone
full pitched on the off stump line, driven to mid-off
cuts in from outside off stump, defended on the front foot

Almost similar to the delivery that took out Taylor. Taibu goes for the off drive and the ball swings in late and goes through the bat and pad gap but misses the off stump. Bravo holds his head in agony
Whack! Taibu responds to the previous delivery by charging out, Bravo drags back the length and outside off stump and Taibu cuts through point
short and climbing outside off, Sibanda goes for the cut but doesn't connect
on the off stump line, defended to short cover region
short in length outside off, kicks up, extra bounce, steered to point
walks forward and across, gets outside off stump, tries to whip the length delivery from outside off through midwicket and is struck on the pad outside off
off cutter outside off, driven to mid-off
moves down the track, tries to flick across the line, misses and the ball rolls off the pad to square-leg region
on the pads, turned behind square-leg
full delivery around off, pushed out to the off side
short delivery, bouncing towards rib-cage, tucked behind square-leg
bounced short on the leg stump line, goes for the pull, top edges it to short fine-leg region
another lifting delivery around the off stump line, Taibu goes for the upper cut, doesn't quite connect properly but gets it over Ramdin
moves forward to push it to the mid-on region
really full delivery, dug out towards midwicket
full in length and outside off stump, left alone
full and outside off, left alone again. 50 for 3, crucial partnership this ..
charges down the track, Sammy shortens the length, pushes it out to the on side
short in length, outside off stump, guided wide of backward point

Sibanda is run out  It was pushed to the off side ... Sibanda sets off for a run before stopping. Too late as Taibu keeps rushing on. Sibanda just stood there as Pollard swoops on the ball. Both batsmen are almost the striker's end. Easy run out . Pollard runs to the non-striker's end to take off the bails.
full and outside off, jabbed off the inner half of the bat to the on side
turns this one to square-leg
gets across, covers his off stump before shouldering arms
waits for the ball to move in before working it to square-leg
full length delivery on the middle and leg, turned to short midwicket
length delivery on the middle stump line, the batsman is late in getting in line but manages to keep it out
lifting delivery outside off and Ramdin gathers
full delivery on the middle and off, jabbed to short midwicket
full in length on the off stump line, runs off the inner half of the bat to square-leg
full delivery on the off stump line, pushed towards mid-on for a quick single. .. there is a direct hit but Taibu is home
full and swinging around the off stump line, just about jabbed away .. again seemed very late in getting forward and almost stumbled out
on the middle and leg line, turned to fine-leg region

Matsikenyeri's misery ends. He never looked in and he is out now. Full delivery on the off stump line, straightening a bit and Matsikenyeri did many things wrong - he was late in getting forward, he stumbled out instead of taking a fluent step, he pushed out blindly, he assumed the ball would come in and lost his off stump.
bouncing delivery outside off stump, left alone
full delivery curving away from the off stump line, pushes inside the line and is beaten
lands on a length outside off stump and moves in with the angle, nothing alarming and so the batsman decides to offer no shot
moves this one on the middle stump line but overpitches it and it has been worked through midwicket
on the middle stump line, length delivery, moves in, turned to long-leg..
walks down the track and turns it past square-leg for a single ..lamb wants a second but Taibu screams at him to get back .. good call
on the middle stump line, tapped to the on side
just outside off stump, the batsman decided to leave it and must have had his heart in his mouth as the ball just about misses the off stump
off cutter from outside off, again Lamb decides to leave it and again, it wasn't all that far away from the off stump. Hmmm....
lands well outside off and moves away further, left alone
around the off stump line and this time Lamb pushes it to the on side
full in length on the middle, driven to mid-off
backs away but mistimes the intended forcing drive to the off side and it has been stopped at cover
short and outside off, cut hard but straight to Pollard at backward point
leans forward to defend the length delivery
full in length on the middle stump line, eased to left of mid-on
Taibu walks down the track, Bravo digs it short and the ball climbs over the intended cut shot and goes to Ramdin
Another short delivery outside off stump, Taibu plays the upper cut but hits it straight to third man. Zimbabwe are really tottering again. What a royal mess they find themselves in.
full in length and on the middle, jabbed away to the on side
on the middle stump line, defended to the leg side
on the pads, clipped behind square-leg
back of length and straightening outside off, he goes for the cut but doesn't connect
full in length around off, leans forward to defend
on the middle stump line, nudged to the off side
outside off stump, short and bounces through to Ramdin
full in length outside off, defended on the front foot
full in length and outside off stump, left alone
this one kicks up from a length, surprises Chigumbura and is hit on his gloves as he shapes to defend
short in length and outside off, beaten on the cut shot
full in length and outside off stump, pushed away on the front foot
on the middle stump line, worked away to square-leg
around the off stump, length delivery, pushed out to cover
cuts in with bounce, jabbed away off the edge
leans forward and across to defend the length delivery
around the off stump line, defended to cover
in the channel outside off stump, tries to run it down to third man and is beaten
short and on the pads, turned down to fine-leg
on the middle stump line, worked away to the on side
around the off stump line, defended off the inner edge to the on side .. he is not getting behind the line
full length delivery outside off, defended to mid-off
really full delivery, almost yorker length, dug out with an open bat-face .. ball runs down to third man
leans forward to defend to the off side
moves in to the middle, dabbed to the on side
strays to the pads, tucked behind square-leg
lovely delivery, straightening outside off, chigumbura is beaten, as he stabs inside the line
runs this one down to third man
fullish delivery outside off, square driven to point
really full delivery , square driven for a single
yorker length on the off stump ;line, dug out to the off side
leans forward to drive to cover
gets forward to drive to mid-off
Whack! . overpitched outside off, creamed through covers
full delivery around off, tapped to the on side
gets forward to play a defensive stroke
length delivery on the middle, tapped to the off side
on the middle, jabbed to the on side
leans forward to defend the full delivery on the middle stump line
on the middle stump line, nudged on the front foot
Thump! He leaned forward on a bent knee and swung it cleanly over long-on! super hit
this one turns away sharply with bounce to beat him comprehensively
taps this one down the track
turns it to square-leg
short in length and outside off, Chigumbura tries to flash it away and is beaten
lands on a good length on the off, rocks forward and defends it to cover
short of a length on middle, worked away through square leg for a single
bowls it on a good length on the off, guided towards third man for a single
targeting middle and off, gets a stride forward and defends it into the leg side
short of a length on the off, slaps it to midwicket
sliding on the leg side, flicked towards short fine leg
worked away off the front foot towards square leg
gets forward, turns the face and turns it towards midwicket
angling in towards middle, dabs it down into the leg side
climbs from short of length outside off, dabbed down to third man
full in length outside off, squeezed out off the outer edge to off side
drags it short, pulled away for a single
from wide of the crease, length delivery, pushed back to the bowler
cut away to left of backward point where Miller makes a neat stop
back of length, bounces outside off, chopped to left of Miller and this time they will get across for the run
leans forward to drive to the off side
tossed on the off and middle, driven down to long-on
And this time the long-off is pinged
quicker one, short in length, punched back to the bowler
quick and skids on straight with the arm, pushed back down the track

After two quick deliveries, Miller slows up the pace,and Lamb pushes  out early and checks his shot and the ball lobs to the right of non-striker and Miller gets across in time with a lunging dive to take the catch
on the middle stump line, worked to short midwicket
runs this short-of-length delivery to third man
full and outside off stump, left alone
outside off stump line, tries to punch it square but doesn't connect
gentle seam-up delivery in the channel outside off, left alone
guides this delivery to point
full delivery, pushed back to Miller
on the middle and leg, skids on to strike the pad on the leg stump line. It would have missed leg stump
floated outside off, gets across to drive to the off side
presses back to punch this one to cover
on the middle stump line, tries to punch it down to mid-on region but Miller intercepts with a dive
around off stump, pushed out to cover
short and wide, cut away easily for three runs. Pollard lets out a cry of agony
on the off stump line, punched out to extra cover
on the off stump line, dabbed to the on side
length delivery in the channel outside off stump, left alone
pushes this one towards point
floated on the off stump line, pushed out to the off side
stays back to punch it to long-on for a single
on the middle and leg, pushed back down the track
full and on the off stump line, driven to cover
turns away from the off stump, tries to punch it to point and is beaten
short and  outside off, cut away to deep-point region
length delivery on the middle stump line, dabbed to the on side
short in length and outside off, cut to point
shout for lbw .. as the ball slides in to hit the pad .. missing leg stump ..the ball rolls to the off side ..
leans forward to drive to the off side
full delivery on the middle and leg, eased to the on side
gets forward to push the length delivery to the on side
turns towards off stump, pushed to point
on the off stump line, punched off the back foot
goes for the sweep and rolls off the pad
on the middle and leg, worked away to the on side
full on the middle and off, driven to cover
on the pads, the ball bounds off the pad
length delivery on the off stump, steered to backward point
in the zone outside off, purposeless waft at it and the ball rushes past the outside edge
pushes this delivery to the off side
full delivery on the middle and off, squeezed off the inner edge past point
mvoes outside leg stump, Rampaul follows him with a yorker, jabbed to the off side
on the off stump line, pushed out to the off side
full in length and outside off, driven off the outer edge down to third man
gets forward to off drive but Gayle, at straightish short cover, makes a diving stop
leans across to defend to the off side
swats this short of length delivery from middle stump past square-leg
on the leg stump line, top edges the sweep to short fine-leg region
leans forward to scoop a full delivery to the off side
on the middle and off, defended on the front foot
bounces into the ribcage, shoveled behind the wicket on the leg side
on the middle stump line, turned behind square-leg
gets forward to block it to the off side
full in length and outside off, slapped away to deep cover
off cutter on the middle and leg line, turned around the corner to long leg
Ah! a boundary. Some action. He just leaned forward to knife through the line and the ball races away between the bowler and mid-off
on the middle and off line, edges the drive to his pad .. there is a shout for lbw but thick edge
leans across to push this one to short cover
on the middle and off, turned to short midwicket
floated outside off stump, lifted over cover ... there is some confusion over the third run as Cremer wants it and turns blindly but is sent back in time
plays the sweep shot to pick up a single
full and straight, pushed quietly back down the track
short in length and bouncing outside off, not much room, the batsman tries to run it down to third man and is beaten
And again. almost an action replay.
similar delivery ,this time jabbed off the edge to the off side for a quick single
full in length and pushed out to cover
leans forward to defend to the on side
Whoa! Violent Thump. He picks this one from outside off and sweeps it really hard to the midwicket boundary ..That was powerfully hit slog sweep.
on the off stump line, defended back to the bowler
around off stump, steered to point
on the off stump line, tapped to the point region
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
gets forward to drive to sweeper cover
Superb hit. He cleared the front foot and pulled the short delivery powerfully over backward square-leg boundary.
leans forward to defend to the off side
length delivery on the off stump line, pushed towards cover
goes for that pull shot again, connects but doesn't clear the deep backward square-leg fielder. Sammy celebrates by pumping his fist .. Good rear-guard action from Chigumbura ends
length delivery on the middle stump line, tapped to the on side
on the off stump line, pushed out to cover
this time he cuts but can't beat the point fielder
cuts again and finds the gap, a single to sweeper cover
on the off stump line, defended to short cover
full delivery outside off, shapes to cut, wrong length and is beaten
leans forward to defend to short cover
on the off stump line, pushed out to mid-off
moves outside leg stump, was thinking about the big hit over the off-side field but ended up shoveling the length delivery to cover. It lobs up for a simple catch.
on the off stump line, leans forward to defend
on the middle stump line, worked to vacant spaces on the leg side for a single
on the leg stump line, moves past the waft to hit the pad
on the leg stump line, short, Price swats it away to fine-leg boundary!
full delivery, goes under the bat and Ramdin collects
leans forward to defend another full delivery
sprays it down the leg side, helped along to the fine-leg boundary
guides this to backward point, wants a single but gets back in time with a dive to beat the direct hit
again some extra bounce on that length delivery, jabbed away
on the middle and off, turned to short midwicket
full in length, on the middle and off, squeezed out to short midwicket
slower one, full, pushed wide of mid-on
length delivery around off stump, defended on the front foot
gets forward to work a length delivery on the middle to square-leg
slips in a wide down the leg side
gets forward to push a full delivery to short midwicket
full and straight - if you miss, I hit as Holding says - Price misses, Roach hits.

inn2.comm: What a cracking shot. Fullish around off stump and Barath goes down on a bent knee to play a lovely looking extra cover drive
turns this to the leg side for a single
good yorker length delivery on middle, dug out to the on side
well outside off stump, ... wide
another one well outside off stump
length delivery outside off stump, left alone
on the off and middle, dabbed to the on side
on the middle stump line, turned to backward square-leg
on the middle stump line, full, eased back to the bowler and Price threatens to throw the ball back
on the leg stump line, edges it to the off side
on the middle stump line, defended to the off side
lovely delivery moving away from Gayle who is beaten, driving inside the line
Wallop. Fullish outside off, Gayle crashes it over mid-off
This one flies over the bowler. Full length delivery on the stumps, Gayle wanted to lift it over mid-on, didn't quite get forward and ended up slicing it right over the bowler
What a loverly hit. Fabulous whippy flick over wide midwicket. Fullish around off and middle stump line and Gayle just leaned forward to play an elegant, yet murderous, whippy shot over the on side
sprays to the leg side, it runs off Gayle's gloves but leg byes given
Flamboyant swing over extra cover. Gayle is da maan. Full in length and outside off, he just knifed through the line/. Up and over she flies. What a over.
turns to the on side for a single
on the middle and leg, turned to square-leg
leans forward to drive down to long-on
backs away to cut but the ball bounces and there is not much room either .. Gayle gets his bat away from the line and keeper gathers
turned to the on side
leans forward to defend
Slam! Gayle continues to indulge himself. Gayle went down on a bent knee to swing it to backward square-leg boundary
skips down the track to defend
around off stump, Gayle has a big swing across the line but doesn't connect
More fun. This time a reverse sweep. He is preparing for IPL i think. He connects well and will pick up a boundary
flatter, around off, pushed out to cover for a single
leans forward to drive to mid-off
on the middle stump line, tapped to on side
picks it around off stump line and sweeps to backward square-leg boundary
leans forward to turn it past square-leg
on the middle and off, worked to square-leg for a single
on the middle and leg, jabbed away to the on side
backs away to the leg side and ends up reaching out for his lofted off drive and is caught right at the long-off boundary. The entertainment is over.
turns away, cut to cover
on the middle and leg, worked past square-leg
gets forward to on drive to long-on
on the front foot, works to midwicket
on the off stump line, defended to cover
on the middle and leg, going with the arm, turned to backward square-leg
on the leg and middle, clipped past square-leg
Dropped by Matsikenyeri  Chanders sweeps it straight to bacwkard square-leg where Matsikenyri makes a complete mess of it. What a clanger
leans forward to push it to the on side
tossed up, turned to the on side
leans forward to on drive eto long-on
outside off stump, padded away
spins with bounce, Chanderpaul holds his bat in side the line
stays back to punch it to long-on
leans forward to defend, misses and the ball lobs up off his pad
leans across to tap the ball to midwicket
Chanderpaul is out. Short in length outside off, Chanderpaul tries to pull it from there but top edges it to mid-on where Price holds the catch
short in length and outside off stump, flashed away off the back foot past the diving point fielder
banged in short, pulls it towards deep square-leg
around off stump, keeps a touch low, Ramdin crouches to keep it out
fullish, on middle and off, defended to the off side
short in length and outside off, mistimes the cut to cover
on the middle and leg, tapped to the on side
turns from leg stump, defended to cover
leans across to flick the leg break over midwicket ....Stylishly and skilfully whipped away
done in by the front-of-the-hand slider. Dead plumb in front. It landed on a length on middle and off line, and went on straight to take him out
on the middle stump line,. pushed back to the bowler
gets well forward to defend
arm ball, moving in on the middle stump line, kept out at the last minute
leans forward to defend on the front foot
another arm ball, pushed out to cover
leans forward to defend to cover
on the middle stump line, on driven through mid-on
on the pads, turned to short fine-leg
leans forward to defend to midwicket
flighted around off stump, driven to mid-off
gets behind the line to defend to the off side

lovely slider .. lands outside off, lures the batsman on the front-foot drive and skids away from him... away from the bat and Taibu breaks the stumps in a flash. Not referred upstairs.. close call .. was the back foot on the line?
stretches forward to defend and the ball hits the pad
charges down the track, takes it on the full and drives through extra cover
on the middle stump line, driven to mid-on
flighted outside off, cut to backward point
quicker one, on the off and middle, pushed to the off side
turns in from outside off, cut away to the off side
outside off stump, quicker one, pushed out to cover
stretches forward to defend down the track
flighted leg break , flicked to midwicket
takes it from outside off, swats it past midwicket
on the leg stump line, runs off the pad
stretches well forward to squeeze it to the on side
moves down the track but drives straight to mid-off
outside off, short in length, pulled to long-on
on the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
tossed up on the middle, pushed out to extra cover
tossed on the leg stump line, goes for the sweep and it rolls away off the pad
stays back to cut the short of length delivery through cover point
leans across to drive to point
backs away to cut to point
leans forward to flick it behind square-leg
gets forward to flick it away to the on side
stays back to push it back down the track
around the off stump, slides away, squeezed off the outer edge
moves down the track to smother the ball
leans forward to drive it through covers
on the front foot, driven to long-on
outside off stump, steered to point
skips down the track to keep out a flighted off break
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
on the leg stump line, swept to short fine-leg
similar delivery, this time swept to right of Price at short fine-leg
goes down the track and goes for a big lofted shot over midwicket but ends up dragging it over square-leg
Stumping missed Lovely flighted legbreak lures Ramdin out .. and he stumbles out almost mesmerised by the fabulous leg break but Taibu doesn't collect it !
drops this short and Ramdin backs away to play a feisty cut shot
on the leg stump line, paddled away
leg break from the leg stump line, dabbed to the on side
on the middle and leg line, worked past square-leg
goes down on a bent knee to play a good slog sweep . He hit that cleanly
goes back to tap the off break on the leg and middle to fine-leg region
stays back to dab it to midwicket
stays back to defend to the off side
flighted around off, squeezed to backward point
goes right back to defend the leg break to the on side
gets forward to defend to the off side

Trapped in front. West Indies continue to be clueless against spin. It landed on a length on middle stump line and just about straightened to hit him right in front. Ramdin was pushing his bat well outside the line. Cremer has really impressed in this series. Very good leggie.
googly on the middle stump line, jabbed away to the on side
Bravo shows quality right away. He moves down the track and plays a lovely uppish on drive over mid-on .. nicely picked up
He goes over the off-side this time .. lofted stroke to the left of long-off
loud appeal for a catch behind .. he got forward to defend and looked as if there was an edge .. Taibu catches it and ..Replay shows it went off the shoulder of the bat
gets forward to work it to the on side
gets forward and across to defend to short-leg
turns to the pad, rolls to right of short-leg
stays back to defend to the bowler

dropped by the bowler What a miss. It was a dipping full toss, Bravo goes for the drive, makes contact with the bottom of the bat and Utseya makes a mess of a return catch. What a dramatic over.. A catch not given by the umpire and another dropped by the captain
stays back to clip it past square-leg
Bravo combusts! It was a flighted delivery around off stump and Bravo goes for an expansive inside-out drive and edges it straight to slip! Good bowling but what a self-destructive streak that was.
on the leg and middle, defended down the track
leg break from the leg and middle, pushed out to mid-on
on the middle and off, worked to midwicket
stretches well forward to defend
presses back to tap it to third-man region
stretches forward and across to defend
backs away to cut it to left of backward point
flighted on leg stump line, swept away to long-leg
leans forward to push it to backward point
turns in from outside off, defended to the off side
gets forward to stab it to cover
gets forward to defend to the on side
around off stump line, pushed out to short cover
flighted leg break, defended on a stretched front foot
googly but short in length and pulled away to deep midwicket
gets forward to block it to the on side
leans forward to flick to midwicket
stretches forward to defend
short in length, quickish off break, whipped past square-leg
on the leg stump line, swept to fine-leg
stays back to punch it to short cover
leans forward and across to defend and is struck on the pad outside off
turns this to short fine-leg
works this one with the turn to midwicket
full again, turned to short midwicket
flighted outside off stump, defended on the front foot
spins in to the middle, tapped wide of midwicket for a single
stays back to punch it to mid-on
leans well forward to defend to the off side
skips down the track to off drive to long-off
Wallop. Flighted googly outside off and Pollard lifts it over mid-off
another googly, hits the pad, going down leg
of course yet another googly - that's what he keeps bowling - defended on the front foot
full delivery, on driven to long-on
short in length, turns away, beaten on the cut shot
on the leg stump line, dabbed behind square-leg .. confusion over second run but both batsmen retreat in time
turns to the off, pushed back to the bowler
